The president and chief executive officer may add names of health professionals, other than those struck off the list by the board of directors, to the list referred to in the first and second paragraphs, if he considers that the number on the list in insufficient. In such a case, he shall inform the board of directors.
The list of the health professionals the Commission may designate for the purposes of section 204 for one year remains in force until it is replaced.


1985, c. 6, s. 205; 1992, c. 11, s. 13; 2002, c. 76, s. 28; 2021, c. 27, s. 62.

